HEADWORD: Perineum
<hw>Per`i*ne"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>peri`naion</grk> about + <grk>peri`neos</grk>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The region which is included within the outlet
of the pelvis, and is traversed by the urinogenital canal and the
rectum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perineurial</ent>⟦br⟧
